t are your thoughts?   </span><hr size=1> I for one umpired baseball for 7-8 years. It helped pay for college and supplied me with some running around money. I will not say I was the best but I know that I worked my butt out trying to be. If I knew I got one wrong or didn't intrepret the rule correctly I did everything I could to reconcile it or changed the call all together. At no point did I feel like or play god. I never looked to see who would win before the game started. I was there for the players. <br>
<br>
That is why I get so pissed when umpires are so incompetent. I am not talking about judgement calls. Most of the time I don't argue on safe or out calls, that is the way they see it. But to often they do not know the rules or are flat not paying attention. To not see a guy who is half way to the next base when the ball is pitched. Or call a ball hit 15 feet over the fence a ground rule double is ridiculous. I have even had an umpire think a SuperDuper was a legal ball. Not to mention be playing ASA and a ball never getting over dick high being called strike two. <br>
<br>
I am aware they have a tough job. I for one go way overboard arguing calls; making that job even harder. But crap this preordained winner, I am the only one who knows what the rules are, by god this is my field attitude has got to go and go now.<br>
<br>
I go to many different places where there are some great umpires. Who hustle and get within 5 feet of each call or are 35 feet into outfield when a ball is hit deep. Are up on all the latest rules. And I salute and show them the respect they deserve but feel like those 3 or 4 at every park who have no clue give the others a bad name.  <br>
<br>
Umpires do have a tough job, but they are getting paid. So in my humble opinion they should earn it. That is the bottom line. If they respect the game and are working hard they will get the respect deserve. <br>
<br>
In the end, those that really work hard hardly ever have problems or people yelling at them. And if for no other reason, if I were still umpiring I know I would work hard to do the best I could just so nobody would be bitching and moaning at me. <br>
