<br>
In most cases these guys don't play. They don't pay attention to the sport, they just show up and call games for money. We need to realize that and realize that you don't get quality umps in those conditions. If the sport were more popular and generated more money, maybe that would change. Until then, I'd say understand the situation and play it. Rarely will an ump actually cost you a game, unless you make a mistake or two to put yourself in that situation.<br>
